Content:
user hey matt miller do you know why there are no keywords or reasons on records from the customerresearch slack channel


agent duncan stewart
 keywords in our current approach we only do initial keyword tagging from user text though we will subsequently highlight relevant terms in agent text since these are all internal messages they are being considered as agent text however we are releasing an update to our keyword logic in a couple of weeks that should fix this
 reasons its not clear why reasons didnt get tagged here there is one record that does have a few and most of the rest have large numbers of suggested reasons so it looks like the confidence just ended up being low in most of the cases i am checking with the team to make sure nothing else is going on though

Content:
user jack divita will enterpret continue creating new reasons ad infinitum im going through and doing the work to merge similar ones but curious if this will be a sisyphean task sweatsmile

agent gt will enterpret continue creating new reasons ad infinitum
yes we do refreshes every two weeks in order to capture insights from new product releases and trends from your users
gt im going through and doing the work to merge similar ones but curious if this will be a sisyphean task sweatsmile
nooooooo sweatsmile think of it more like weeding your garden than pushing your stone
you are correct in that technically the list will continue to grow over time but i promise you that merging reasons together is incredibly high leverage to improve the quality of your instance and we are actively investing in better tooling to learn from the types of merges you make along with better automated deduplication

user oh boy i appreciate the reframe but it sure feels like pushing a stone right now sweatsmile

agent yeah thats fair
i would be happy to help andor hear your feedback on what is time consuming about it today  we want to make this process easier

user  the wait time to see the changes reflected in the dashboard isnt great since i feel like i still see the clutter while it processes on the backend its helpful that they turn grey
 the prediction of which reasons to merge is quite good the search works well and having both the search and the prediction feels quite effective
 there are so many reasons that have only been applied to  ticket and which have very subtle name differences eg help inviting members vs help inviting members in notion vs help inviting members in notion workspace maybe for some products this would be a helpful distinction but some concept in the model of everything is going to be part of notion or part of a notion workspace you do not need to differentiate between these concepts could go a long way
 sometimes the customers dont use the same words as we would to describe a feature we get reasons with their wording and with our wording ive merged some of these to use our wording but i have a feeling that more will keep popping up with the customers wording would be great to clearly indicate these sorts of conversations are actually all about this concept  label the reasons accordingly our clearest example is for a feature called allowed email domains which lets users automatically join a notion workspace as members in tickets this mostly shows up as complaints about i tried to add  as a guest but they popped into being a member how do i fix it and the reason is called something like issue with unexpected guest adding behavior when im reviewing the dashboard i need to understand that our product is behaving properly and these are not bug reports ive relabeled for now to be more like help understanding allowed email domain feature since thats a category that will make more sense for our product teams

agent elliya cutler  thank you so much for this feedback
looping in a couple folks from my team to make sure this doesnt go to waste
vivek kaushal is our product manager and is designing our next generation of taxonomy you should start to see some changes in q  vivek lets make sure we are taking in to account elliyas feedback
ansup babu is our machine learning lead working on reason deduplication ansup  can we run the new deduplication script on notions data i suspect it would be able to catch many of these examples provided by elliya
arnav sharma is our cto  fyi on some current pain points with managing the taxonomy

user running a dedupe script would be incredibly helpful no rush slightlysmilingface appreciate you listening

agent if we shared a spreadsheet offline sometime next week where you could go through and confirmdeny our automated suggested merges would that work

user sure i was trustingfrustrated enough to just let you merge them sweatsmile

Content:
user hi jack divita i was wondering if it was possible to measure the sentiment change within a ticket for example does a customer start with negative sentiment but has positive sentiment at the end of a ticket

user do we ask for csat multiple times within a tickets lifecycle i thought we only ask it when the ticket is closed

user nope we only ask for the csat  hours after the ticket is solved for email twitter tickets will receive the csat every time the ticket is solved but we can adjust as needed

user nice is what enterpret calls sentiment different from csat i thought they were the same 

user i was looking at the customer sentiment throughout the entire ticket not their csat survey the thought behind this one is that wed be able to find tickets tickets where the support team turned the customers interaction around

user right so what enterpret calls sentiment is different from csat

user jack divita please correct me on this but enterpret user sentiment analyzes the customer sentiment through the ticketinteraction satisfaction rating will be the customers response to the csat survey

agent gt please correct me on this but enterpret user sentiment analyzes the customer sentiment through the ticketinteraction satisfaction rating will be the customers response to the csat survey
this is exactly correct

user thanks jack divita do you know if it would also be possible to track the sentiment change within an interaction

agent currently not possible but this is not the first time we have heard this request have raised it with the engineering team and there will be exploration on the feasibility in the coming weeks

user thanks if this gets added to the roadmap can you let us know this could be a useful metric for us

agent definitely
before being added to the roadmap we will likely have some follow up questions on use cases and specific examples any additional detailsthoughts you can share on those would also be helpful

user of course no problem
 positive gt negative
  does this lead to churn
  are there policies that are causing this change 
  these can also be used to identify coaching opportunities
 negative gt positive 
  identify tickets where an agent did an good job can be used to improve training or feedback for the agents

agent gt  does this lead to churn
this one is doable today without analyzing intraticket sentiment changes we just need a little more data from notion

agent meaning  if you tell me which of your users churned and when i can tell you what problems they had before churning and how those compared vs users who have not churned
this is a very common use case today

user in order to tell you which users have churned and when wed probably have to pull subscription changes in from stripe which is managed by my team jack divita do you have any additional information about howwhat youd need from us to get churn data into enterpret i can ask my engineers if they have time for it

agent the only thing i need is something to join it agains the feedback record for zendesk it looks like we have user email unique user id workspace id external user id for gong we have workspace id user id and email for forethought all i have is a record id
i would also recommend including other additional metadata that might be useful for analysis sign up date churn date churned arr number of seats churned etc

Content:
agent hey fred kang toby laforest  varun told me that you are working on a project to analyze closed lost in order to try and identify feature requests that might influence more won deals mitch louie shared with me an extract of closedlost deals over the last  months that i uploaded to enterpret and we can use to look at common requests and to comparecontrast vs deals that were won
here is a link to the first iteration of the dashboard to help with this i added some filters to the charts to try and highlight reasons that to me seemed actionable 
a couple of highlights that stood out to me
 the ability to search through contracts comes up in lost deals twice as often as won deals
 redlining documents comes up x as often in lost deals
 setting reminders for contracts comes up x as often in lost deals
 a clause library comes up x as often in lost deals
 ocr on contracts seems is also a common one on lost deals
i am imagining this as an iterative process where we can continue to drill in to some of these reasons to make them more specific and further filter the list so it is as useful for you as possible
im excited to help start with this process and keep going from here  let me know your thoughts

user thanks jeremy and jack more details
 were specifically looking to examine our tickets that are coming in from zendesk that are type bug or feature request  not interested in general question stripe action or admin action

 we have a list of  specific descriptions of notion product areas a few examples synced blocks the wiki function database sorting page deletion and wed love to map that on top of all of the data we have in enterpret right now our engineers use those tags to determine if a specific area of the product is becoming buggier than we have a tolerance for

agent amazing  we should be able to do all of this

user sure whats a good format for you

Content:
user hello wave
 
 heres a report on 
 
 mag saved search   complaints
 spiralcalendarpad weekly report  march    march  
 ballotboxwithballot feedback count  feedback on linears issue category reveals that users are experiencing difficulties with various integrations uploading images logging in creating issues and using filters there are also concerns about the complexity of jira and issues with the linear app itself problems with integrations users have reported issues with connecting to github      slack     and sentry   these problems range from syncing and setting up integrations to triggering them and creating new issues theres also an issue with importing from jira  records  with users unable to add a new synchronized project or editchange the linear team   difficulties uploading images theres a persistent issue with uploading images  records on linear     despite the support teams followups the problem seems to persist even after refreshing the app login issues users have reported an issue with login  records to linear    despite attempts on both pc and mobile and even after following suggested troubleshooting steps users are unable to log in challenges creating issues users have reported an issue with creating issues  records    they face difficulties with the issue creation process using slack and have to resort to the standalone linear app to create features and bugs limitations with filters users have reported an issue with filters  records   they find limitations in filtering and configuring the board for different components and have difficulty with combined filters complexity of jira users have reported an issue with jira being complex  records   they find it inefficient in managing projects and access rights and express a preference for github issues issues with linear app users have reported an issue with linear app  records    they face persistent problems with linear despite refreshing the local database and not using any proxy or vpn view saved search button

agent brian hendery sarah barnekow we have updated our slack summary format to improve the quantification and bring it in line with what is now in the tool would love to hear your thoughts on this and it could be a good time to give this another try to see if its a useful tool i set up a general search on complaints for this example and brian the gold nuggets language that you didnt like is also gone sweatsmile

Content:
agent hey team please find some feedback from float will add the gong call in the replys
thanks for your understanding on the call  looking forward to staying in touch
heres some of our teams verbatims from the trial
gt heres my early thoughts  questions on enterpret as im going through
gt  so it pulls and creates summaries from our customer feedback channels based on keywords we specifically tag or can it tag automatically based on the nature of customer feedback eg if were not tracking agency or billable hours it can still search  create a summary based on that pretty powerful if so edit it can thats awesome this feature alone will solidify amp finalise my agency positioning work raisedhandsskintone
gt  i love that the feedback summary can be created based on feedback from a specific time period last  months is the perfect preset for what im working on
gt  the sentiment analysis is brilliant too  being able to see  filter based on this is very helpful for answering questions about why people did or didnt switch to float  how were currently serving a particular group
gt  email subscription is a great win too as itll help centralise insights in a given period in one place so i can share them internally
gt 
gt 
gt 
gt 
gt curious to learn about its analytics and reporting capabilities  how confident do we feel we can trust the data and summaries it provides us especially if were going to be making key big product x marketing bets from this
gt  quantify  sum of mrr x feedback reason  this is gold showing the mrr impactchurn from each feedback reason is powerful enables us to build better features x marketing that serves our best fit customers
gt  segmentation is a key component here though would like to see how far we can drill into each reason and split it by market segment use case mrr etc
gt 
gt 
gt 
gt 
gt overall i think its better than what we have for sure based on its centralised customer feedback analysis features unsure how much it costs but i imagine its a lowtomid figure acv product based on the functionality on show here
gt 
gt questions to ask here to move forward from my perspective
gt  does it require someone to manually feed the model every week to continue getting good results eg building the taxonomy and merging reasons into perpetuity etc seems like a timeconsuming job for a poor soul sweatsmile
gt  how can we use it to help inform our product x pmm okrs like figma did at company level
gt  for queries that are hyperspecific and new eg timezones etc the data amp summaries it provides will certainly be more surfacelevel compared to items around billing allocations other core product features
gt  can this be replicated with a customgpt from open ai could we feed it all our data and have it spit out what we need
gt 
gt 
gt 
gt 
gt other than that i think its very powerful  we just need to set it up right
gt the summary inevitably endup me wanting to know more
gt 
gt example
gt  issue with adding project dates
gt the summary returned

Content:
user jack divita vivek kaushal sending a little inspiration your way i am testing out using chatgpt to analyze some old survey data i uploaded the csv with the prompt provide a summary for the most common things that are keeping people from remote recording today include counts when possible the response it gave me back was very much the sort of response i was expectingdesiring to get back when testing out the new wisdom experience in enterpret

user heres the response
gt the analysis of survey responses regarding whats currently keeping people from remote recording today reveals a wide variety of reasons with each unique reason mentioned by only one respondent indicating a high degree of specificity and diversity in the barriers faced here are some insights based on the data
gt  unique reasons there are  unique reasons mentioned for not recording remotely some of these include not having the function yet procrastination uncertainty about where to record not being ready to coordinate with others needing an easier solution not having equipment and just not getting around to creating content of this kind
gt  keyword insights by analyzing the frequency of words used in the responses after removing common stopwords we find several key themes
gt  need  mentions a significant number of respondents indicate a need for something possibly resources information or capabilities that they currently lack
gt  time and preparation  mentions combined words like yet  time  havent  and no  suggest that issues related to timing readiness and availability of resources are common barriers
gt  technical and process uncertainty  mentions of how the frequency of the word how suggests that uncertainty about the process or technical aspects of remote recording is a barrier for some
gt  procrastination and motivation the mention of procrastinating as a reason along with the implicit suggestion of delay in words like yet and havent points to procrastination or a lack of motivation as factors
gt 
gt these insights indicate a complex landscape of barriers to remote recording including technical challenges lack of resources timing and readiness issues and motivational factors each respondent appears to have a unique set of challenges underscoring the need for tailored solutions to address these barriers

agent really appreciate the inspiration and the feedback here mike mcnasby prayskintone
cc arnav sharma cto

agent mike mcnasby thanks for sharing
doing a quick comparison against wisdom today here was the response
the analysis of user feedback reveals that the most common issues preventing users from remote recording on descript are related to linking and using squadcast audio quality logging into squadcast and uploading recordings
 issues linking and using squadcast with descript users have reported an issue with linking squadcast to descript records  and an issue with recording with squadcast records       they have faced difficulties with the integration of squadcast and descript such as the edit in descript feature and issues with the squadcast feature of descript    
 poor audio quality in squadcast users have reported an issue with audio quality in squadcast records during remote recordings      they have experienced audio issues including weak connection choppy video and audio and syncing issues     users have also reported significant audio delay and frequent video freezing issues
 difficulties logging into squadcast users have reported an issue with logging into squadcast records which is a part of their remote recording setup         they have faced trouble logging in issues with linking their descript and squadcast accounts and problems with logging in after deleting their google account
 troubles uploading recordings on squadcast users have reported an issue with uploading recordings on squadcast records         they have faced trouble uploading local recordings on descript for their squadcast guests issues with uploading a recording from squadcast to descript and problems with video uploading rendering time lag and poor audio quality


agent agreed  chat gpt did a better job of understanding the intention of the question revolved around keeping people from remote recording today but chatgpt wont give you the citations to see the quotes themselves

agent but even having the ciations in this case i assume is actually not as useful because we didnt quite understand the question correctly  we anchored on general complaints remote recording instead of focusing on what users said was preventing them from using it

agent hey heath rogers here is an overview of generally how sentiment is calculated on our platform
one thing i would like to note  personally i am not a huge fan of sentiment analysis my view is that sentiment outputs tend to not be very actionable as far as understanding root causes let alone potential solutions to customer problems  whereas the outputs of our reasons are meant to be descriptive and actionable
i am curious what you are hoping to use the sentiment reporting for my guess is that we can do the same thing and better by using the output of some of our more descriptive models

Content:
user were seeing a weird mismatch between our zendesk tickets and how enterpret visualizes the tickets
specifically on zendesk we see a big spike in tickets on feb  see nd image but through enterpret it looks like theres not a spike until feb 
what could be driving that difference
 is there a day lag in when enterpret gets the tickets
 if not what else could be driving this difference
 does this only assess sentiment analysis on first contact or does each subsequent contact get a sentiment analysis
would love your thoughts on this jack divita

user molly jane nicholas do you know if the zendesk tickets are looking at ticket creation date or ticket resolution date

user laura perea heath rogers do either of you know the answer to the above

user kait schorr has been looking into the snowflake gt enterpret pipeline and might have a pov

agent this delay wouldnt be coming from our side that being said at a glance i suspect the root cause is that you are sending us the close date as the created date

user im looking into this more today ill focus on zendesk differences this is helpful

user im going to put together a doc of my findings for both sources and hopefully we can find someone to own it long term so we dont have the ambiguity around troubleshooting feel free to send me any details or weirdness youre observing

user fwiw my hypothesis is the state in which entepret ingest the tickets is different from the state in which zendesk is reporting the ticket dates

user the state of the ticket itself i think i remember someone maybe you mentioning that i will investigate that angle as well

user this is already helpful all it does seem clear that its related to the state and not some weird issue with incorrectly tagging so ill communicate that back to the team

user molly jane nicholas i dont know that was one of my questions norman lemke can you work with kait schorr on this

user the mode dash should be by creation date norman lemke to confirm

user so if enterpret is indeed close date it would be nice to switch that to match jack divita michael nguyen

user i would also be very interested in seeing sentiment on creation date and sentiment of close date to see if there was a change throughout the life cycle of the ticket

agent kait schorr when looking at the snowflake table there will be two date fields that are required by us for ingestion
 erccreatedat the creation timestamp of the feedback
 ercrowcreatedat the creation timestamp of the row in the table helps enterpret track what data to ingest
can you confirm that on your side the erccreatedat is being mapped to the created date of the ticket itself
here is the link to the full documentation of our snowflake integration if that is helpful


user yes looking now

user so erccreatedat is actually using the updatedat date of the ticket

user also the zendesk tickets are also being filtered by the feedbackprohibiteddomains table

agent kait schorr can we correct the dates we can help run a backfill on our end also is that the only filter on the table 
michael nguyen do we still need the prohibited domains filter
would it be possible to connect love sometime this week id want to make sure we are all on the same page and that any updates we make fully solve the problem so that we are not still working through this a few weeks from now 

user the filters ive found are these
userid is not null
ticket status in closed solved hold
userfacts domain not in prohibited domains

user one thing to note is we are in the middle of pulling data for an exec review meeting tomorrow so unless its a quick fix we should hold michael nguyen jack divita

user  madison kohls perhaps we can capture this request to change the erccreatedat to be the date the ticket was created not the updatedat date in your current doc of proposed changes to the query

user michael nguyen yup this seems to be from a model built downstream of the query i am proposing it seems like regardless we need to change the field from updatedat to createdat in this downstream model

user which query are you proposing changing madison kohls

user nvm norman lemke sent it to me we should definitely set up some time to align on this

user yes let me find a time for us michael and norman so i can give better context smile

Content:
agent hi everyone wave sharing an end of week recap as there are a lot of exciting things going on between figma and enterpret right now
ever since we integrated the zendesk ticket data we have seen a dramatic increase in the interest in enterpret from all of you figmates this week had really great training onboarding sessions with heath rogers and folks from your team and madison kohls as representation from the billing team
for anyone else who might be interested in getting started with enterpret i have included two links below that i think will be useful for you all first is a  minute overview video that will cover all of the basics of what you need to know to get started and second is my calendar link along with an open invitation for anyone at figma who might want to ask some questions and have more of a guided onboarding
link to video overview of enterpret 
calendar link to schedule personalized product onboarding 
i also wanted to highlight some ongoing work from our team
 molly jane nicholas has created some really amazing dashboards highlighting the feedback on the recent dev mode launch there are also a number of subscriptions directly pushing summarized insights to some teamspecific slack channels  this is exactly how we recommend taking advantage of feedback during product launches
  have a home page where everyone can align on the same data  trends
  automate pushing insights to slack so that people can stay up to date on whats going on without having to run their own reports allowing them to deep dive if they see something interesting
  to checkout her dashboard follow this link here
  
 there are some gaps in the zendesk data that we are working through all of the analysis you can do in enterpret will be correct but there is a chance it is not fully complete as we are not ingesting every single support ticket you can follow along with the progress in the thread linked below
  
 this week we launched the beta version of our chat interface called wisdom  this will allow you to ask questions and learn from your customer feedback through normal natural language as opposed to constructing a query through our ui
  i have attached an example of what this type of interface looks like
  if you are interested in participating in the beta product launch please let me know and i will add you
if anyone has any questions or ideas please do not hesitate to reach out  we love to hear from you all

Content:
agent hey kayla eliaza jeremy bui great catching up today to talk through our usersaccounts modeling available in enterpret summarizing our call below
tldr  you can sync user  account metadata to enterpret to enable advanced reporting on customer feedback for example
 understanding the revenue impact of different reasons for feedback
 understanding root causes behind user churn
 understanding major causes for friction in user onboardingactivation 
the easiest way to set this up is to start syncing this data to us through census the documentation for setting this up is included below you can sync any type of metadata to us as a part of this sync the most important part is that we have a primary key that we can use to join against your existing feedback data from zendesk we are receiving a variety of different ids along with the user email but it sounds like the best one to use would be the notion user id  which we are receiving in two different formats which i have highlighted in the example below  these two fields seem to be populated on about  of zendesk tickets we have received in the last  months
enterpret record link 
zendesk ticket link 
external user id baafaacbbefbebb
unique user identifier baafaacbbefbebb
link to documentation

Content:
agent michael nguyen starting this thread to follow up on something we were chatting about the other day  i think we need a clear definition and owner of the snowflake tables that are currently being ingested into enterpret
 we need clarity on what data is being analyzed and even more importantly what data is not being analyzed
 we need to know who to go to when we want to make changes to the data model
 a from my conversation with the support team this week there are new dimensions of metadata that we would want to bring in
currently there are two snowflake tables that are being brought in to enterpret
 snowflake customerfeedbacktickets
  database name enterpretshareddata
  this is zendesk data
 snowflake customerfeedbackreviews 
  database name enterpretshareddata
  customer feedback reviews table name customerfeedbackreviews
  these are asana feedback tickets govoc
for both sources we are ingesting a value for ercid which best as i know represents the unique id for each record on the figma side based on previous conversations i know that we are not being sent every single record for each of these sources  but it is not clear what the criteria being used to determine what records are sent to us even if we do not change this definition i think it will be very helpful for everyone involved if we can atleast share this definition
i have included some analysis from my side to help with this investigation but ultimately we will need someone from the figma data engineering team to own this for the zendesk erc ids they appear to be sequential and make me think that you are sending us roughly  of tickets the asana ticket ids do not appear to be sequential
spreadsheet with extract of ticket ids 
who would be the right person to ask about this and to own this moving forward from the figma team is there any other data i can provide from the enterpret side to help with this

user hey jack thanks for putting this together i will hop in and help figure this out or at least hunt down an owner

agent amazing  thank you so much
please let me know if there is anything else i can do to help

user thank you so much kait schorr this is gonna be a huge win for us prayskintone

user looking into the asana tickets so customerfeedbackreviews and they arent actually incremental they are randomly generated unique numbers so the gaps between the numbers doesnt signify missing tickets the ercid is indeed the task id number though and you can only see it when youre using asana in the browser its the last bit of the url

user yup but see examples in previous threads where we are missing some tickets and we dont understand why

user understood im still digging into it just wanted to share that finding since the spreadsheet was calculating the jumps between asana tickets as well im looking at the queries and i will trace them from the source and see wherewhy things are dropping off

user for the asana tickets anything from the following domains is filtered out according to the query

user as well as only tickets generated in this project
id 
name voc needs

 fine tune taxonomy for more granular and actionable outputs
  now that the taxonomy is fully customizable i recommend we follow a thorough and systematic approach by tackling key areas one by one sequentially i am happy to help put in work on this front to help guide but i cannot be the one making the tactical decisions on reason definitions
  i will never know your business and your priorities as well as you all who would be best for me to work with on this front mitch louie should this be me and you
 nail down core use cases
  manjit toor i want your monthly support summaries to be as automated as possible using this template should get you  of the way there do you agree
  
 expand to more core use cases
  julia bendix i know there are other executive reports outside of monthly support tickets that you were hoping to be sharing can you share some examples of what those might be
 expand to decentralized insight production
  at our other customers we have seen voc have a lot of success by sponsoring dedicated enterpret training sessions with product support and operations stakeholders anyone who might have some use for customer feedback in their day to day we spend  minutes together and by the end of it people know how to create their own reports and find their own insights
  i think we should be aiming to start running sessions like these by late februaryearly march when we have spent some more time fine tuning the taxonomy
  julia bendix how do you feel about that timeline any initial thoughts on who some of these teams who might benefit most from using feedback first hand would be

Content:
agent duncan from propelleraero thoughts and feedback about his use of enterpret and taxonomy 
his journey as a insight consumer pm starts usually at keywords  feedback records  open in search  scroll each feedback record cursorily  read through summary post this he checks if the summary is relevant from his tribal knowledge in many cases it is sparse insights that he is able to derive from this like  he is sure that issue with ability to export data and need for ground control points assistance users are seeking help with ground control points  are not applicable in context of the keyword here  google earth
all in all he is very happy with the summaries direction as it is efficient for him to read multiple summaries and extract meaningful insights from that as opposed to rabbit holing in quantify land one nit that he had though was that feedback generally starts from x records but quotes show a very lesser number of feedback records y as part of summary where yx his expectation was that itd be aggregate validated xx
his general user journey is keywords  feedback records  open in search  scroll each feedback record cursorily  read through summary post this he nuances this as part of a coda doc wherein he adds eg eg eg examples of summary quotes or favorited feedback records in a doc and finalizes a breakdown doc which can then be used by pmsursdesigners in his areas to pick up discovery for ss attached
for taxonomy 
 keywords are very useful but there is a lot of keywords that are redundant or unusable due to being very broad in nature there is no capability to hierarchically manage these
 he was pretty gungho about reasons initially but found them to be too broad in many cases even if granular reasons are present they are not top of mind due to the attribution of records towards broader reasons being really up the pecking order
 he had heard from the team on parentchild relation of keywords and reasons as part of t wasnt sold on the idea but when i took him through the broad idea of customisable nodes which can have  to many relationship  he mentioned he was excited about the direction as this might reduce the noise a lot
 he would want this relationship to be autogenerated as admining the taxonomycleanup merges creations is something he hates as a pm and would ideally need ai to fill that gap
 he commented that currently reasons and keywords operate in a standalone manner but should be more contextual and mappable again not by humans but by ai
 he also mentioned that each feedback record shows a lot of incorrect predictions for categories even when he starts from a completely different keywords in place and this is misleading and erodes his trust on the tool ss attached
i also updated him on oracle and he was super excited for this as  paraphrasing  for me to uncover insights by querying in natural language and see just not text but list of feedback records visualizations summaries in a single chat like interface is the direction which seems the most intuitive to me post having the relationships as part of taxonomy improvements im assuming the models would have a lot more context about keywords reasons and their own relationships
hed be happy to provide feedback from alpha stages if required

agent this is awesome saurabh arora thanks for sharing did we get any insights on who consumes duncans coda doc and why
was the call recorded by any chnce

agent this is consumed downstream by user researchers designers for discovery 

agent got it curious about why these researchesdesigners dont feel the need to visit enterpret to read feedback about whats identified  read adjacent feedback

agent there is an additional layer of product sense and investigation required by duncan post finalizing the items he hands over to the research teams
Reasons: Happy With Summaries, Issue With Taxonomy

Content:
agent brian hendery sarah barnekow a little experiment i did this afternoon 
i pulled some of the user and account data from intercom records that are in enterpret and set up a sample user  account sync to see if it would yield any interesting insights one thing that i found is that the top improvement suggestions change quite a bit when weighted by account data in this example by the number of seats in other words potential seat impact of an improvement ability to assign tasks to multiple people jumps from rd to out in front by a wide margin while the ability to create custom fields drops to the bottom a number of reasons drop out of the top  completely replaced by new ones here are the charts
  by feedback count
  by potential seat impact
if this kind of analysis might be interesting we can discuss more tomorrow about setting it up via census with a proper recurring sync
a number of our customers have decided to set this up and many are already getting value out of it and we have decided to postpone any discussion on this being a paid feature and are opening up access for free to all customers for the foreseeable future

 export feedback data from enterpret and assemble a list of users
 filter your source table to include only users with a matching feedback record
 set up the data sync from the filtered source table to enterpret
